Schenck, 1859
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,364,821]" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1437749150" collectionCode="IUCN" county="Vulnerable" location="Central Asia" municipality="Fennoscandia" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" specimenCount="1">
<taxonomicName box="[151,350,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusus">
<emphasis box="[151,350,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">Bombus confusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a disjunct distribution in Europa and 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:616887B9FF85FFA2FF3CFEF8FB2FFCD0:EC1E6074FF85FFA2FCFBFEB1FC6FFE60" box="[848,993,364,389]" county="Vulnerable" municipality="Fennoscandia" name="Central Asia" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">Central Asia</location>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ornosa" box="[1012,1370,364,389]" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" refString="Ornosa, C. &amp; Ortiz-Sanchez, F. J. (2004) Hymenoptera: Apoidea I. In: Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cientificas (Ed.), Fauna Iberica. Fol. 23. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CSIC, Madrid, pp. 1 - 556." type="book chapter" year="2004">Ornosa &amp; Ortiz-Sánchez 2004</bibRefCitation>
). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:616887B9FF85FFA2FF3CFEF8FB2FFCD0:EC1E6074FF85FFA2FADBFEB1FA12FE60" box="[1392,1436,364,389]" county="Vulnerable" municipality="Fennoscandia" name="The" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">The</location>
western population is spread across 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:616887B9FF85FFA2FF3CFEF8FB2FFCD0:EC1E6074FF85FFA2FD83FE4DFDF2FE42" box="[552,636,400,423]" county="Vulnerable" municipality="Fennoscandia" name="Europe" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">Europe</location>
, with the exception of 
<collectingMunicipality box="[890,1044,399,424]" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">Fennoscandia</collectingMunicipality>
and the British Isles. It has already disappeared from large part of its range, and therefore, it is assessed as 
<collectingCounty box="[1008,1131,436,461]" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">Vulnerable</collectingCounty>
in the 
<collectionCode box="[1221,1289,436,460]" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">IUCN</collectionCode>
Red List of European Bees (Rasmont 
<emphasis box="[442,499,471,496]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">et al.</emphasis>
2006, Rasmont 
<emphasis box="[682,738,471,496]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">et al.</emphasis>
2015).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,364,821]" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1437749164" collectingDate="1800" collectingDateMax="2000" collectingDateMin="1800" county="Coniferae forest" elevation="1050" location="eastern Pyrenees. Nevertheless" municipality="Rasmont" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Navarra">
In the Iberian fauna, 
<taxonomicName box="[437,567,508,532]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusus">
<emphasis box="[437,567,508,532]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">B. confusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very rare (
<figureCitation box="[740,808,508,533]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1474,1496]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,882,1445]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[150,1436,873,1451]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 5. Map showing historical locations (●) of Bombus confusus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322693/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) and a threatened species that suffers regression (
<tableCitation captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="25.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,332,1115]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="TABLE 3. Bumblebee species and subspecies in the Pyrenees from historical data with no records in the contemporary sampling and the corresponding IUCN Red Lists category (from Spain: Verdú &amp; Galante (2006), Verdú et al. (2011) and from Europe: Rasmont et al. (2015): Not Evaluated, NE; Endangered, EN; Vulnerable, VU; Data Deficient, DD; Least Concern, LC). The number of individuals collected in historical samplings in the Pyrenees and information about the last record in the Iberian Peninsula are included." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/BDBE6627FF84FFA3FF3CFF45FDE1FED5" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" tableUuid="BDBE6627FF84FFA3FF3CFF45FDE1FED5">Table 3</tableCitation>
): eigth individuals were observed from 1 980 until 1991, at isolated points of the Pyrenees and 
<collectingRegion box="[1246,1336,544,567]" country="Spain" name="Navarra" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">Navarra</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[1352,1421,543,568]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1474,1496]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,882,1445]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[150,1436,873,1451]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 5. Map showing historical locations (●) of Bombus confusus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322693/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), from 
<quantity box="[213,379,580,605]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" unit="m" value="1050.0" valueMax="1500.0" valueMin="600.0">
<elevation box="[213,379,580,605]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" unit="m" value="1050.0" valueMax="1500.0" valueMin="600.0">600 to 1500 m</elevation>
</quantity>
, on cleared areas of 
<collectingCounty box="[611,793,580,605]" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">Coniferae forest</collectingCounty>
and alpine pastures. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rasmont" box="[1030,1212,580,604]" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" refString="Rasmont, P. (1988) Monographie ecologique et zoogeographique des Bourdons de France et de Belgique (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Bombinae). Faculte des Sciences agronomiques de L´Etat, Gembloux, 310 pp." type="book" year="1988">
<collectingMunicipality box="[1030,1130,581,604]" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">Rasmont</collectingMunicipality>
(1988)
</bibRefCitation>
found it in a higher altitude, 
<date box="[250,418,615,640]" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" value="1800" valueMax="2000">
<collectingDate box="[250,418,615,640]" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" value="1800" valueMax="2000">
1800 and 
<quantity box="[362,418,616,640]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000</quantity>
</collectingDate>
</date>
m, in some records of a couple of localities in the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:616887B9FF85FFA2FF3CFEF8FB2FFCD0:EC1E6074FF85FFA2FC49FDB5FACFFD65" box="[994,1345,615,640]" county="Coniferae forest" municipality="Rasmont" name="eastern Pyrenees. Nevertheless" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" stateProvince="Navarra">eastern Pyrenees. Nevertheless</location>
, several of the scarce Iberian records were based on individuals from 1900 or from 1980’s (Ornosa 2011), where it has not been collected again due to habitat transformation into cereal crops. In 2012, Castro (pers. comm.) found an individual outside the Pyrenees, further inside the Iberian Peninsula.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,364,821]" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">
The Pyrenean 
<taxonomicName box="[366,499,760,784]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusus">
<emphasis box="[366,499,760,784]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="65">B. confusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was assessed as Endangered (EN) in the IUCN Spanish Red List (Ornosa 2011) (
<tableCitation box="[158,245,796,821]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="25.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,332,1115]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="TABLE 3. Bumblebee species and subspecies in the Pyrenees from historical data with no records in the contemporary sampling and the corresponding IUCN Red Lists category (from Spain: Verdú &amp; Galante (2006), Verdú et al. (2011) and from Europe: Rasmont et al. (2015): Not Evaluated, NE; Endangered, EN; Vulnerable, VU; Data Deficient, DD; Least Concern, LC). The number of individuals collected in historical samplings in the Pyrenees and information about the last record in the Iberian Peninsula are included." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/BDBE6627FF84FFA3FF3CFF45FDE1FED5" pageId="24" pageNumber="65" tableUuid="BDBE6627FF84FFA3FF3CFF45FDE1FED5">Table 3</tableCitation>
). Regardless, strict measures for the protection to this species are urgently required.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
